TITLE      : ARexxBox - ARexx Interface Design Tool
VERSION    : 1.00 - first public release
AUTHOR     : Michael Balzer (balzer@heike.informatik.uni-dortmund.de)
DISTRIB.   : FD software, (C) 1992 Michael Balzer
REQUIRES   : OS2.04 or better, reqtools.library, amiga.lib 37.32
HOST       : amiga.physik.unizh.ch [130.60.80.80]  (or mirror site)
DIR        : /amiga/devel
FILENAME   : arexxbox100.lha
DESCRIPTION:

ARexxBox (inspired by the GadToolsBox) is a programmer's tool for
designing ARexx interfaces for your programs, with the special goal
to greatly simplify this procedure while implementing the standards
suggested by the User Interface Style Guide.

With ARexxBox, you can design any ARexx interface by just
describing it's commands and their arguments and results.
ARexxBox will then generate all the standard code you need to
implement this ARexx interface, all you have to do is insert
some lines of code to interface to your program.

ARexxBox _and_ the generated code will only run on AmigaOS 2.04 
(or better). The ARexxBox (but not the generated code) needs the
reqtools.library by Nico Francois.

The generated source code should be compilable by any common ANSI
compatible C compiler.  For linking you will need at least
version 37.32 of the amiga.lib (amiga_lib 37.32 (12.11.91),
included in the Native Developers Upgrade Kit 2.0 V37.4 11/91).

You can get the ARexxBox via anonymous FTP from
amiga.physik.unizh.ch (or one of its mirror sites), directory
/amiga/devel.

